 it from the Wardha and Wainganga rivers. The hills generally run east to northeast, with the northern slope mild and the southern side steeply dropping down suddenly. The plateaus and slopes of the hills were formed millions of years ago, during the Carboniferous period. Tourists may visit the holy temple of Lord Shiva at the cave temple Gupt Mahadev on Mahadeo Mountain, one of Pachmarhi's three highest locations. In addition to Gupt Mahadev, this temple also has Bade Mahadev, a shrine devoted to Lord Shiva. These temples are highly regarded and extensively worshipped. Your senses will be calmed by the easily visible view of nature and the surrounding greenery. Time: 24 hours. Free entry. Destination: India's Satpura Range, Pachmarhi Required time estimate: 2 to 3 hours. About 10 KM away from Pachmarhi Bus Stand. Treks close to Bhopal help everyone, whether they are nature lovers, adventurers, or just those searching for a break. 5. Handi Khoh: The 300-foot-high sheer rock creates the best ravine in the nation. Handi Koh is surrounded by thick forests and flowing waters, and mythical tales are related. It is said to have previously been a large lake, but the wicked snake protecting it was killed by Lord Shiva's fury, and the lake was reduced to a little pot (Handi). It is one of the most beautiful sights in Pachmarhi to visit because of the beautiful nature and enjoyable journey. Time: Every day of the week from 7 AM to 5 PM. No entry fee is required. Address: 461881 in Pachmarhi Cantt, Madhya Pradesh. The recommended time needed: 1 to 2 hours. Distance from Pachmarhi Bus Stand: 5 km. The greatest way to travel is by road; find out where to go on a road trip close to Bhopal. 6. Dhupgarh: Tourists will be impressed by the view from the top of this mountain, which is the tallest in the Satpura mountainous region. The summit provides views of the smaller Satpura mountains and Vindhya mountain and the top view of the water flowing. This plateau has a heavenly appearanc