r a permit is INR 1250, while the cost for a gypsy is INR 2100. Destination: Hoshangabad, Madhya Pradesh, 461001, India; Satpura National Park. It will take around 6 hours, or half a day, if going on a safari. Two hundred ten kilometres from Pachmarhi Bus Stop. Staying at a jungle resort close to Bhopal is the best option if you want a closer look at the city's vibrant wildlife and adventurous attractions. 4. Mahadeo Hills: Mahadeo Hills is located on the northern border of the Narmada basin, separating it from the Wardha and Wainganga rivers. The hills generally run east to northeast, with the northern slope mild and the southern side steeply dropping down suddenly. The plateaus and slopes of the hills were formed millions of years ago, during the Carboniferous period. Tourists may visit the holy temple of Lord Shiva at the cave temple Gupt Mahadev on Mahadeo Mountain, one of Pachmarhi's three highest locations. In addition to Gupt Mahadev, this temple also has Bade Mahadev, a shrine devoted to Lord Shiva. These temples are highly regarded and extensively worshipped. Your senses will be calmed by the easily visible view of nature and the surrounding greenery. Time: 24 hours. Free entry. Destination: India's Satpura Range, Pachmarhi Required time estimate: 2 to 3 hours. About 10 KM away from Pachmarhi Bus Stand. Treks close to Bhopal help everyone, whether they are nature lovers, adventurers, or just those searching for a break. 5. Handi Khoh: The 300-foot-high sheer rock creates the best ravine in the nation. Handi Koh is surrounded by thick forests and flowing waters, and mythical tales are related. It is said to have previously been a large lake, but the wicked snake protecting it was killed by Lord Shiva's fury, and the lake was reduced to a little pot (Handi). It is one of the most beautiful sights in Pachmarhi to visit because of the beautiful nature and enjoyable journey. Time: Every day of the week from 7 AM to 5 PM. No entry fee is required. Address: 461881