d relaxing weekend trips. Pachmarhi is home to several magnificent and enchanting attractions, such as mysterious caves, ancient temples, and silvery waterfalls. We've put up a list of attractions in Pachmarhi, Madhya Pradesh, so that you may depart with a suitcase full of fascinating memories and stunning photos. 1. Pandava Caves: One of the most prominent sights in Pachmarhi is a series of five stone temples surrounded by naturally occurring gardens and crudely carved columns and pillars. These beautiful caverns are veiled in various legends from many historical periods. They were last hewn by Buddhist monks who utilized them for meditation since the natural way greatly helped them. The most widely spread legend is that the Pandavas stayed in these caverns during their exile, becoming known as the Pandav Caves. Time: Every day of the week, 8 AM to 6 PM. Entry is not charged. Destination: 461881 in Madhya Pradesh, Pachmarhi, India 1 to 2 hours are ideally needed. About 2 KM away from Pachmarhi Bus Stand. Resorts in Bhopal provide everything you need to make a boring day into an exciting one if you choose to spend your days and evenings in a relaxed mood. 2. Bee Falls: Imagine huge amounts of water falling gracefully from a height in the middle of a beautiful forest. One of the most well-known attractions in Pachmarhi is Bee Falls, and after you've descended the many stairs and arrived at the waterfall, it's impossible not to be in awe of it. Around the fall, you can discover little sellers sending snacks and tea. You may not only relax and enjoy the scenery, but you can also dive into the natural freshwater pool and enjoy a swim. Height: 35 meters. Location: Bee Fall Road, Pachmarhi, Madhya Pradesh, 461881, India. Entry fee: INR 15 for each adult Indian. Best Time to Go: any time of the year, go during the monsoon to experience a lot of rain and relax in the pool during the summer. The Pachmarhi Bus Stand is around 3 KM Water Parks in Bhopal allow you an escape from the heat in the most enjoyable way when temperatures rise, so jump in a pool and beat the heat. 3. Satpura National Park: This national park is located in Madhya Pradesh's Hoshangabad district and is spread out over the Satpura Hills. The Sanskrit word "Satpura," which means "seven hills," was given to the chain of hills in the central Indian highlands. It is a 524 square kilometre region that is a component of the Pachmarhi Biosphere Reserve. The deep gorges and undiscovered jungles of Satpura National Park are home to many species, including Water Buffaloes, Leopards, Elephants, Barasingha, Honey Buzzards, and Malabar Pied Hornbills, Paradise Flycatchers, and the rare Rhesus monkeys. Times: 7 AM to 6:30 PM, seven days a week. Entry Fee: The cost for a permit is INR 1250, while the cost for a gypsy is INR 2100. Destination: Hoshangabad, Madhya Pradesh, 461001, India; Satpura National Park. It will take around 6 hours, or half a day, if going on a safari. Two hundred ten kilometres from Pachmarhi Bus Stop. Staying at a jungle resort close to Bhopal is the best option if you want a closer look at the city's vibrant wildlife and adventurous attractions. 4. Mahadeo Hills: Mahadeo Hills is located on the northern border of the Narmada basin, separating it from the Wardha and Wainganga rivers. The hills generally run east to northeast, with the northern slope mild and the southern side steeply dropping down suddenly. The plateaus and slopes of the hills were formed millions of years ago, during the Carboniferous period. Tourists may visit the holy temple of Lord Shiva at the cave temple Gupt Mahadev on Mahadeo Mountain, one of Pachmarhi's three highest locations. In addition to Gupt Mahadev, this temple also has Bade Mahadev, a shrine devoted to Lord Shiva. These temples are highly regarded and extensively worshipped. Your senses will be calmed by the easily visible view of nature and the surrounding greenery. Time: 24 hours. Free entry. Destination: India's Satpura Range, Pachmarhi Required time estimate: 2 to 3 hours. About 10 KM away from Pachmarhi Bus Stand. Treks close to Bhopal help everyone, whether they are nature lovers, adventurers, or just those searching for a break. 5. Handi Khoh: The 300-foot-high sheer rock creates the best ravine in the nation. Handi Koh is surrounded by thick forests and flowing waters, and mythical tales are related. It is said to have previously been a large lake, but the wicked snake protecting it was killed by Lord Shiva's fury, and the lake was reduced to a little pot (Handi). It is one of the most beautiful sights in Pachmarhi to visit because of the beautiful nature and enjoyable journey. Time: Every day of the week from 7 AM to 5 PM. No entry fee is required. Address: 461881 in Pachmarhi Cantt, Madhya Pradesh. The recommended time needed: 1 to 2 hours. Distance from Pachmarhi Bus Stand: 5 km. The greatest way to travel is by road; find out where to go on a road trip close to Bhopal. 6. Dhupgarh: Tourists will be impressed by the view from the top of this mountain, which is the tallest in the Satpura mountainous region. The summit provides views of the smaller Satpura mountains and Vindhya mountain and the top view of the water flowing. This plateau has a heavenly appearance thanks to the rocky scarps, ravines, and clefts, yet this mountain is still less popular than other Pachmarhi tourist attractions. Some key attractions here are the Dhupgarh Fall and the tranquil surroundings. Time: a full day. Entry is not charged. Location: Satpura Mountain Range, Pachmarhi, Madhya Pradesh, India. Required time estimate: 2 to 3 hours. About 10 KM away from Pachmarhi Bus Stand. Amazingly, whether you are a couple that believes in the delicacy of romance or a pair looking for adventure and pleasure, Dhupgarh may create the ideal date for you. 7. Priyadarshini Point (Forsyth Point): The name Forsyth Point derives from the year 1857 when Captain Forsyth made the discovery. It's amazing to see hills layered on top of one other and covered with clouds and mist. One of the few tourist attractions in Pachmarhi that can offer such breathtaking beauty is Priyadarshini Point. It is only a 400-meter walk to the viewpoint from the parking space. Time: a full day. Entry is free of charge. Destination: Pachmarhi, Madhya Pradesh, India, next to MPTDC Barriol. The recommended time needed: 1 to 2 hours. The actual distance from Pachmarhi Bus Stand is 7 KM. Investigate the tranquil destinations close to Bhopal to spice up your journey. 8. Rajat Prapat (Silver Fall/Big Fall): Rajat Prapat seems to be a silver strip that plunges into the forests as it descends an about 350-foot-high cliff. To view the fall from one end of the mountain, you must first trek uphill for a short while. Once you reach the top, you will see the stunning Satpura hill range in the distance, with the fall being surrounded by greenery. Rajat Prapat is one of the wonderful places to visit in Pachmarhi. 107 meters in height. The district of Hoshangabad is in Madhya Pradesh, India. Entry is not charged. Any time of day, after a monsoon, or in the winter are the ideal times to visit. About a 3 KM hike is expected to get to Apsara Vihar from the Pachmarhi Bus Stand, followed by a 3 KM trek to the falls and back to Apsara Vihar. Adventure activities close to Bhopal give another dimension that has the potential to improve your trip to Madhya Pradesh in addition to the numerous destinations that are the travel destinations of many travellers. 9. Chauragarh Temple: Chauragarh Temple is located at the top of Chauragarh, nestled between a lush valley and undulating trees. The respected shrine is known as Chota Mahadeo, devoted to Lord Shiva, and is another name for this temple. It is not simple to get there since one must climb a route of around 1250 steps, but if you do, you will undoubtedly be rewarded with the greatest surrounding views. Visit one of Pachmarhi's holy sites to capture beautiful scenery photos with you