t the Pandavas stayed in these caverns during their exile, becoming known as the Pandav Caves. Time: Every day of the week, 8 AM to 6 PM. Entry is not charged. Destination: 461881 in Madhya Pradesh, Pachmarhi, India 1 to 2 hours are ideally needed. About 2 KM away from Pachmarhi Bus Stand. Resorts in Bhopal provide everything you need to make a boring day into an exciting one if you choose to spend your days and evenings in a relaxed mood. 2. Bee Falls: Imagine huge amounts of water falling gracefully from a height in the middle of a beautiful forest. One of the most well-known attractions in Pachmarhi is Bee Falls, and after you've descended the many stairs and arrived at the waterfall, it's impossible not to be in awe of it. Around the fall, you can discover little sellers sending snacks and tea. You may not only relax and enjoy the scenery, but you can also dive into the natural freshwater pool and enjoy a swim. Height: 35 meters. Location: Bee Fall Road, Pachmarhi, Madhya Pradesh, 461881, India. Entry fee: INR 15 for each adult Indian. Best Time to Go: any time of the year, go during the monsoon to experience a lot of rain and relax in the pool during the summer. The Pachmarhi Bus Stand is around 3 KM Water Parks in Bhopal allow you an escape from the heat in the most enjoyable way when temperatures rise, so jump in a pool and beat the heat. 3. Satpura National Park: This national park is located in Madhya Pradesh's Hoshangabad district and is spread out over the Satpura Hills. The Sanskrit word "Satpura," which means "seven hills," was given to the chain of hills in the central Indian highlands. It is a 524 square kilometre region that is a component of the Pachmarhi Biosphere Reserve. The deep gorges and undiscovered jungles of Satpura National Park are home to many species, including Water Buffaloes, Leopards, Elephants, Barasingha, Honey Buzzards, and Malabar Pied Hornbills, Paradise Flycatchers, and the rare Rhesus monkeys. Times: 7 AM to 6:30 PM, seven days a week. Entry Fee: The cost for a permit is INR 1250, while the cost for a gypsy is INR 2100. Destination: Hoshangabad, Madhya Pradesh, 461001, India; Satpura National Park. It will take around 6 hours, or half a day, if going on a safari. Two hundred ten kilometres from Pachmarhi Bus Stop. Staying at a jungle resort close to Bhopal is the best option if you want a closer look at the city's vibrant wildlife and adventurous attractions. 4. Mahadeo Hills: Mahadeo Hills is located on the northern border of the Narmada basin, separating it from the Wardha and Wainganga rivers. The hills generally run east to northeast, with the northern slope mild and the southern side steeply dropping down suddenly. The plateaus and slopes of the hills were formed millions of years ago, during the Carboniferous period. Tourists may visit the holy temple of Lord Shiva at the cave temple Gupt Mahadev on Mahadeo Mountain, one of Pachmarhi's three highest locations. In addition to Gupt Mahadev, this temple also has Bade Mahadev, a shrine devoted to Lord Shiva. These temples are highly regarded and extensively worshipped. Your senses will be calmed by the easily visible view of nature and the surrounding greenery. Time: 24 hours. Free entry. Destination: India's Satpura Range, Pachmarhi Required time estimate: 2 to 3 hours. About 10 KM away from Pachmarhi Bus Stand. Treks close to Bhopal help everyone, whether they are nature lovers, adventurers, or just those searching for a break. 5. Handi Khoh: The 300-foot-high sheer rock creates the best ravine in the nation. Handi Koh is surrounded by thick forests and flowing waters, and mythical tales are related. It is said to have previously been a large lake, but the wicked snake protecting it was killed by Lord Shiva's fury, and the lake was reduced to a little pot (Handi). It is one of the most beautiful sights in Pachmarhi to visit because of the beautiful nature and enjoyable journey. Time: Every day of the week from 7 AM to 5 PM. No entry 