elf there from Mahisasur, another mythical figure. You will see a natural Shiva Lingam as you enter the cave, worshipped by tourists from all over the nation as it stands in the shadow of a large rock. One of the popular tourist destinations in Pachmarhi, Jata Shankar Cave, offers a singular experience for each tourist. Monday to Saturday, 7 AM to 7 PM. Entry is not charged. Address: 461881 Jatashankar Rd, Pachmarhi, Madhya Pradesh There is a time requirement of about 1.5 hours. The distance from Pachmarhi Bus Stand is 5 kilometres. In addition to the well-known temples and historical structures, Madhya Pradesh is home to various caverns that will pique your interest. 11. Apsara Vihar Waterfall: A picnic with friends and family would be the perfect activity at this beautiful waterfall and pool. It is a well-liked attraction in Pachmarhi that will have you fascinated with the site for hours. After a 10-minute downhill hike to get there, you may satisfy your hunger at the stalls selling snacks and tea. People may be seen diving and taking dips in the tiny pool, which gathers the chilled water from the fall. The people gave the pool the name Apsara Vihar because they frequently observed English ladies swimming there while the British ruled the country, who looked to them like fairies. The height of Apsara Vihar Waterfall is 9 meters. Location: Near Jaistambh, Hoshangabad District, Pachmarhi, Madhya Pradesh 461881, India. Wandering in the jungle and hiking. Entry fee: An adult must pay INR 50 to enter the forest. From October to May is the best time to visit Apsara Vihar Waterfall. About 2.6 KM, including a 1.5 KM-long ascent, from the Pachmarhi Bus Stand. 12. Pachmarhi Catholic Church: On Sunday mornings, you may go there for prayer and church. It's a tranquil haven. This church only opens on Sundays since there aren't many Catholic families living in or around Pachmarhi. The church's attractiveness is defined by its old-world aesthetics, tinted windows, neo-gothic alt